<br>
I just dinged 24 last night and picked up the rest of my self only gates. My poor Treant Faction really took a hit though... Hehehe. Now apprehensive from amiable after 250+ kills. Oh well, I am a wizard, so I need druids like I need a third ball. <br>
<br>
Anyway... Due to RL work schedule being haywire, I wont be able to play much with my regular group. My plan is to hunt at the spires in SK when I can get a group. Or I might try soloing the Evil Eyes in the gorge... I am currently bound at Kurns Tower in the Feild of Bone. Can any of you give me an idea or two concerning other viable places I can hunt for 2-3 hours a night? I will be playing from midnight to 3am EST if that matters (re: pick up groups). <br>
<br>
I love dungeons, but usually only go with my regular group. Lowbie dungeons on Druzzil are usually pretty empty, so BYOG is a definate must, most of the time. I am looking to make 29 withen a week or so and loot is definately a consideration. I also have all of my self only gates, so travel is no problem.<br>
<br>
Thanks in advance!<br>
<br>
Your friend in flames,<br>
<br>
Lysandor V<br>
24 HIE Wizard - Druzzil Ro<br>
Deefnders of the Rose<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uadonborealis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Adon Borealis</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_yellowspot.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/31/01 11:25:04 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.legendsofmarr.com/membersonly/memberspictures/Adon.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I Just made 24 (hooray!) need a &quot;where to hunt&quot; please</span><hr size=1> the lake of ill manners...er omen is a good place at that level for pickup groups...and with the right group the exp is unmatched.<br>
<br>
 <p>Adon Borealis <BR> War Priest of Tunare <BR> Nerf Druids</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/unerachniathewitch.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nerachnia The witch</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/31/01 11:43:38 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I Just made 24 (hooray!) need a &quot;where to hunt&quot; please</span><hr size=1> Here is what I did<br>
<br>
Dalnir if you want pick up groups.... very popular on my server.<br>
<br>
The bard at Nk spires is still decent xp if i remember correctly.  <br>
<br>
Gnolls at the spire rock if you can get a partner<br>
<br>
And if you are a glutton for danger and dungeons...... find a Pick up group for najena or go solo in Sol A for a while ...at the entrence to sol A.  But i am just a sicko so may not want to try that.<br>
<br>
Nerachnia<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ucaldavien.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Caldavien</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/31/01 11:44:29 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Good solo Exp.</span><hr size=1> If you have Jboots or dont mind begging sow you can do whet I did. Go quad kite the sarnaks in LOIO. You can start at 24 when you get COL and keep on till 30 or so. Just pull the ones that pop at the tower at the back door or thew ones that pop in the tower thats half way to the front door. Then just circle them till they are in a tight cluster and kite them up and down the valley between that middle tower and the zone. DO NOT pull from the front door for quadding. I died ALOTtrying that. This is a great tactic for fast lvling from 24 to 29. Thge only thing that stops you is no SOW or lack of mana, I recommend you pull on mob and try to kill it with COL before you try a quad. If you dont have mana for 1 then you cant do 4 <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . Give it a shot its a great way to solo once you get it down pat. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwhizbangdustyboots.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Whizbang Dustyboots</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/31/01 11:47:41 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I Just made 24 (hooray!) need a &quot;where to hunt&quot; please</span><hr size=1> There's actually a ton of things to hunt in South Karana, if you're willing to roam around looking. This is made easier if you have a tracker partner, of course. A bard would be ideal -- Selo's, mana song and Tracking ... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umarttog.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Marttog</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/31/01 11:52:42 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Good solo Exp.</span><hr size=1> For those levels I did a number of spots (I like to travel)<br>
<br>
Lake of Ill Omen was good.  I liked to camp at that the tree on the NW corner of the lake.<br>
<br>
Dalnir was a lot of fun for pick-up groups.  Forget about soloing there.  However, it was often sparsely populated.<br>
<br>
The SK Spires were good as well, although often heavily camped.<br>
<br>
The goblins on Oracle Island and the gargoyles on the next island were a lot of fun too.  When the rest of the gobbies turned green, I starting camping the Headmaster.<br>
<br>
Unrest was also a good place for pickup groups. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ulysandor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lysandor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/1/01 9:38:40 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I Just made 24 (hooray!) need a &quot;where to hunt&quot; please</span><hr size=1> Thanks for the great replys folks...Bound myself near the giant fort last night in WW. At 24th level I can solo giants for fun and exp... My friends are amazed! Plus I can try to get a group in Dalnirs...<br>
<br>
SK gnolls and other great EXP mobs are just a port away. This is really ideal. I appreciate the help!<br>
<br>
/salute<br>
<br>
Lysandor Verantics<br>
25th level wizard of Felwithe<br>
Defender of the Rose<br>
Druzzil Ro <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uryzak620.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ryzak620</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/1/01 1:36:33 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Solo Spots</span><hr size=1> If I remember right.......the Hermit in SK is a pretty easy kill, fast spawn, and gives exp up to Lvl 28.  He's a root/nuke kind of spawn.  To get him out of the hut, say<br>
&quot;I will kill you&quot;.  Say that right next to the chimney.  Drops FS every once in awhile, and also drops some pp every now and then. I soloed him from 24-28 (i think).  Haven't been to SK in quite some time, so I don't know if that's still considered a &quot;hot&quot; camp or not. But because he's a ranger, he has low HP, very wimpy spells, and if you can get root to stick, he's toast. One warning....while medding invis yourself, cause there are a couple of roaming gnolls around the area that can be a pain.  When you say &quot;I will kill you&quot; to the hermit, make sure you vis up.  <br>
Another thing to solo till about 27/28 are the Tentacle Terrors in Najena.  IMHO, slightly tougher than the Hermit, but very manageable.  Hope this helps <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Ryzak Myrdhyn<br>
52 Channeler<br>
Rodcet Nife <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uswansontoo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Swansontoo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/1/01 3:57:52 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Solo Spots</span><hr size=1> Easiest thing i found to fly through your 20's is to Bind in Lake omen on FM zone line. Just lfg in Omen if none which is rare port to NK grab a sow from someone on bridge. Run to either Aviaks,Gnolls,Paw, or Treants. Even hit OT if you have to. My 22 Cleric has great luck in either OT or Lake Omen.<br>
<br>
Swansontoo<br>
Channeler of the 52nd Nuke<br>
